      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the high-revving 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant, utilizing VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a precise, short-throw linkage. The IMS bearing has been proactively addressed with a ceramic retrofit, and the cooling system has been refreshed with a low-temp thermostat. The chassis retains its factory-spec handling characteristics, featuring a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, while braking is managed by four-piston monobloc calipers over ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. This example is a mechanically sound driver with a linear power band and a stiff, communicative chassis, perfect for the purist seeking a visceral analog experience.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 26
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
